This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object detection using lidar-based point clouds. It also involves the use of a modified version of YOLOv2, which is a popular object detection algorithm in the computer vision community. 

The paper also falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it is related to autonomous driving, which is a major application area for robotics. 

The paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of a complex regression strategy to estimate multi-class 3D boxes. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with the development of a state-of-the-art real-time 3D object detection network, which is a key component of autonomous driving systems. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves the use of natural language processing techniques to describe the proposed method and the experimental results.
